metrics_conclusion: Beautiful Stranger has higher complexity than the average song  in terms Chord Complexity and Chord Progression Novelty.
key_conclusion:
Beautiful Stranger is written in the key of C♯ Mixolydian.  

According to the Theorytab database, it is the 9th most popular key among Mixolydian keys and     the 40th most popular  among all keys. The C♯ Mixolydian scale is similar to the C♯ Major scale except that its 7th note (B) is a half step lower.  Mixolydian chord progressions are heavily featured in many genres of music like classic rock, which relies on the major chord built on the 7th scale degree. 

See the C♯ Mixolydian Cheat Sheet for popular chords, chord progressions, downloadable midi files and more!

metadata.editComments: Added vocal melody of entire first verse. Fixed some syncing issues.
Changed the part entirely to the actual pre-chorus. Chorus and Intro/Dah Dahs to follow

Very difficult to analyze section, because of all the major chords. I have chosen to retain the C# Mixolydian perspective because it always goes home to a C#7 sound, but I could equally see an argument for E Major or B Major as well.

This part serves as the Intro and Chorus Lead-Out. Again, strange ambiguity with exactly what key we are in. The "dah-dah" chromatic step down is a nice tactic. From the 3rd of F#, to the 1 of A, to the 5th of C#.
